## 🛠 Technical Implementation

### System Requirements

**Minimum Hardware:**
- CPU: 8+ cores, 3.0GHz+
- RAM: 16GB (32GB+ recommended)
- Storage: 50GB+ free space
- GPU: Optional (CUDA-compatible for acceleration)

**Software Stack:**
- Python 3.10+
- Ollama with Llama 3/CodeLlama models
- CrewAI framework
- Advanced mathematical libraries

### Installation & Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/cicciopanzer27/Multi-Hemisphere-AI-Theory-Development-System.git
cd Multi-Hemisphere-AI-Theory-Development-System

# 2. Install Ollama
curl -fsSL https://ollama.ai/install.sh | sh

# 3. Download required models
ollama pull llama3
ollama pull codellama
ollama pull mistral

# 4. Set up Python environment
python -m venv venv_crewai
source venv_crewai/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv_crewai\Scripts\activate

# 5. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 6. Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your Ollama configuration

# 7. Run the system
cd meta_ignorance_project
python src/meta_ignorance_project/main.py
```

### Configuration Options

```python
# config.py
OLLAMA_HOST = "http://localhost:11434"
MODEL_NAME = "llama3"
MAX_EVOLUTION_CYCLES = 20
CONSCIOUSNESS_FIELD_RESOLUTION = 0.001
SIGMA_LANG_COMPLEXITY = "advanced"
THEORY_VALIDATION_DEPTH = "comprehensive"
```

